The paper proposes a new method for image instance segmentation, specifically for segmenting individual glands in colon histology images. This task involves identifying and segmenting individual instances within an image, which is a problem that has become increasingly important in recent years. The proposed method leverages deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, and incorporates side supervision to guide the learning process. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as well as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep learning for image analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
